release.name: v7.0.1
release.body:
## Changes
## 🚀 Features

* Restore collection loop (#2533) @asolntsev
* restore method `$$.isEmpty()` (#2533) 
* restore support for "self" field in Container (#2534) @asolntsev
* simplify creation of custom collection conditions (#2531) @asolntsev
* #2372 rename `CollectionCondition` to `WebElementsCondition` (#2533) @asolntsev

## 📦 Dependency updates

* Bump commons-io:commons-io from 2.14.0 to 2.15.0 (#2532) @dependabot

pull_request.body:
restore 2 methods:
1. `$$.iterator()`
2. `$$.isEmpty()`

I still think these tests should not be used in tests.
But they are widely used, so we had to make a compromise.

commits.message:
restore support for "self" field in Container

Now you need to declare your own field of type `SelenideElement` and annotate it with `@Self`.

commits.message:
simplify creation of custom collection conditions

Now the minimal implementation only requires users to implement method `check`.

#2372 Fix deadlock in static initialization of collection conditions

to solve this problem, we renamed base class from `CollectionCondition` to `WebElementsCondition`.

move default implementation of `missingElementSatisfiesCondition()` to base class

now custom collection conditions don't need to implement this method (in most cases).
